<TITLE> UK expulsion of Russian diplomats political-Russia </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 MOSCOW, July 23 (bdnews24.com/Reuters) - Britain's expulsion of four Russian diplomats because Moscow refused to extradite a man suspected of murdering ex-KGB agent Alexander Litvinenko was politically motivated, a senior Russian prosecutor said on Monday. Britain's reaction was "plainly groundless, inappropriate, unjustified and lies exclusively in a political framework," Alexander Zvyagintsev, Russia's deputy Prosecutor-General, told a news briefing. "We refused extradition on the basis of the law." Britain has accused ex-KGB agent Andrei Lugovoy of killing Litvinenko last year in London with radiation poisoning, but Moscow has refused to send him to London, saying it would break its constition. Zyagintsev's comments follow a story in the London-based Sunday Times newspaper which reported that top British government officials believed Litvinenko's murder was "state sponsored terrorism". Russian Foreign Minister Sergei Lavrov and Britain's ambassador to Moscow have both tried to play down the rhetor
